---
<BaseLayout title="API Docs" description="n0brains Signals API documentation — endpoints, authentication, rate limits, and response formats.">
  <script type="application/ld+json">{JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "WebAPI",
    "name": "n0brains API",
    "description": "REST + WebSocket + Webhook + MCP server API delivering scored crypto intelligence signals — whales, funding, liquidations, on-chain flows, options + ETF + stablecoin flows, macro bias, security feeds, X (Twitter) curated feed, and more. Each signal includes direction, urgency, confidence, and quality band. MCP endpoint drops into Claude Desktop, Cursor, Cline. Analytical data only, not financial advice.",
    "url": "https://n0brains.com/docs/",
    "documentation": "https://n0brains.com/docs/",
    "termsOfService": "https://n0brains.com/terms",
    "provider": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "n0brains",
      "url": "https://n0brains.com"
    },
    "offers": [
      { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Free tier — 60 req/min, REST only, 15-min delay" },
      { "@type": "Offer", "price": "19.99", "priceCurrency": "USD", "description": "Pro tier — 600 req/min, real-time, REST + WebSocket + Webhooks + MCP server (12 tools, Claude Desktop / Cursor / Cline)" }
    ],
    "potentialAction": {
      "@type": "SearchAction",
      "target": "https://api.n0brains.com/signals?asset={asset}&signal_type={type}",
      "query-input": "required name=asset"
    }
  })}</script>
  <section class="docs-page">
    <h1>API Reference</h1>
    <p class="docs-subtitle">Base URL: <code>https://api.n0brains.com</code> &middot; All responses are JSON &middot; Timestamps are Unix epoch (seconds)</p>

    <div class="card legal-card">
      <h2 id="not-advice">This is analysis. It is not financial advice.</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>Everything n0brains publishes — signals, scores, reference prices,
        invalidation levels, target levels, paper-trading results, the
        <code>trade_signal</code> action hint, the <a href="/proof">/proof</a>
        page, all of it — is n0brains' own algorithmic analysis of public
        market data.</strong> It is provided for informational purposes only.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>It is <strong>not</strong> investment advice, a recommendation, a solicitation, a
            personalized strategy, or any form of advisory service.</li>
        <li>It is <strong>not</strong> tailored to your portfolio, risk tolerance, or
            jurisdiction. The same data is published to every subscriber.</li>
        <li>Reference levels are <strong>analytical pivots</strong> derived from order-book
            S/R or models — not instructions to enter, exit, or stop a trade.</li>
        <li>n0brains does <strong>not</strong> execute trades, hold custody of funds, or act
            as a broker, adviser, or fiduciary.</li>
        <li>Past performance — including the simulated results on
            <a href="/proof">/proof</a> — does <strong>not</strong> guarantee future results.
            Signals can and will be wrong.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>You are solely responsible for every trading decision you make and
        for any profits or losses that result.</strong> By using this API you accept
        the full <a href="/terms">terms of service</a>, including the limitation
        of liability in §8.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2 id="quickstart">Quick Start</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><a href="/signup">Create an account</a> — get your API key instantly</li>
        <li>Set the header <code>X-API-Key</code> on every request</li>
        <li>Hit <code>GET /signals</code> — you are done</li>
      </ol>
      <pre><code>curl -H "X-API-Key: intel_sk_your_key" https://api.n0brains.com/signals</code></pre>
      <p class="docs-tip">Running an OpenClaw agent? Just hand it your API key and the base URL — it will figure out the rest. Tell it: <em>"Use the n0brains API at https://api.n0brains.com with X-API-Key intel_sk_your_key"</em> and let it trade. More — including an optional skill file — on the <a href="/agents/">agents page</a>.</p>
      <p class="docs-tip">Want to know how the signals have performed under different exit rules (trailing stop, no-SL, US-hours-only, etc.)? See the <a href="/docs/strategies">Strategy Library</a> — backtested reference configurations on real 1-minute candles across three exchanges.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2 id="auth">Authentication</h2>
      <p>All authenticated endpoints require an API key via the <code>X-API-Key</code> header. Keys are generated on registration and can be rotated via <code>POST /auth/api-keys</code>.</p>
      <p>Login also returns a JWT token usable via <code>Authorization: Bearer</code>.</p>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Header</th><th>Example</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>API Key</td><td><code>X-API-Key</code></td><td><code>intel_sk_a1b2c3...</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td>JWT Token</td><td><code>Authorization</code></td><td><code>Bearer eyJhbGci...</code></td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2 id="rate-limits">Rate Limits</h2>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Tier</th><th>Requests/min</th><th>Signal Delay</th><th>Access</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Free</td><td>60</td><td>15 minutes</td><td>REST API only, limited fields. MCP <code>tools/list</code> open for catalog discovery.</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Pro</td><td>600</td><td>Real-time</td><td>REST + WebSocket + Webhooks + <a href="/docs/mcp">MCP server</a>, full fields</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <p>Rate limit exceeded returns <code>429</code> with a message pointing to the upgrade page.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2 id="endpoints">Endpoints</h2>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Method</th><th>Path</th><th>Auth</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/health</code></td><td>None</td><td>Liveness check</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/signals</code></td><td>API Key</td><td>List active signals (filterable)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/signals/{'{id}'}</code></td><td>API Key</td><td>Single signal detail</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/signals/similar</code></td><td>Pro</td><td>Semantic nearest-neighbor search</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/narrative/{'{coin}'}</code></td><td>Pro</td><td>Narrative heatmap for asset</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/manipulation/{'{coin}'}</code></td><td>Pro</td><td>Manipulation score for asset</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/trust/{'{coin}'}</code></td><td>Pro</td><td>Trust &amp; scam score for token</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/levels/{'{coin}'}</code></td><td>API Key</td><td>S/R levels from Hyperliquid</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/market-opens</code></td><td>API Key</td><td>Session opening prices</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/macro</code></td><td>API Key</td><td>Macro Pulse — latest BTC + ETH directional bias</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/macro?history=N</code></td><td>Pro</td><td>Macro Pulse historical snapshots (last N reports, max 30)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/performance</code></td><td>None</td><td>Public win rate / PnL stats</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-post">POST</span></td><td><code>/auth/register</code></td><td>None</td><td>Create account</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-post">POST</span></td><td><code>/auth/login</code></td><td>None</td><td>Login</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-get">GET</span></td><td><code>/auth/me</code></td><td>API Key</td><td>User profile</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-post">POST</span></td><td><code>/auth/api-keys</code></td><td>API Key</td><td>Generate new API key</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-del">DEL</span></td><td><code>/auth/api-keys/{'{id}'}</code></td><td>API Key</td><td>Revoke API key</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-post">POST</span></td><td><code>/billing/checkout</code></td><td>API Key</td><td>Stripe checkout session</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-post">POST</span></td><td><code>/billing/portal</code></td><td>API Key</td><td>Stripe customer portal</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-post">POST</span></td><td><code>/webhooks</code></td><td>Pro</td><td>Register webhook</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-del">DEL</span></td><td><code>/webhooks/{'{id}'}</code></td><td>Pro</td><td>Remove webhook</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-ws">WS</span></td><td><code>/stream</code></td><td>Pro</td><td>Real-time signal stream</td></tr>
          <tr><td><span class="method method-post">POST</span></td><td><code>/mcp/</code></td><td>Pro (tools/call); open (tools/list)</td><td>MCP server — 12 read-only tools for Claude Desktop, Cursor, Cline. See <a href="/docs/mcp">/docs/mcp</a>.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2 id="signals-endpoint">GET /signals</h2>
      <p>Returns active signals, optionally filtered. Free tier receives signals with a 15-minute delay.</p>
      <h3>Query Parameters</h3>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Param</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>asset</code></td><td>string</td><td>Filter by ticker (e.g. BTC)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>signal_type</code></td><td>string</td><td>regulatory, whale, sentiment, price, hack, listing, macro, macro_pulse, liquidation, funding, other</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>direction</code></td><td>string</td><td>bullish, bearish, neutral</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>urgency</code></td><td>string</td><td>high, medium, low</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>limit</code></td><td>int</td><td>1-200 (default 50)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>offset</code></td><td>int</td><td>Pagination offset (default 0)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>include_opens</code></td><td>bool</td><td>Include market opening prices (default true)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>min_confidence</code></td><td>float</td><td>Minimum confidence score (0.0–1.0, default 0.0)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>min_score</code></td><td>float</td><td>Minimum signal score (default 0.0)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>band</code></td><td>string</td><td>Filter by trade quality band: A+, A, B, C, D</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>min_trade_quality</code></td><td>float</td><td>Minimum trade quality score (0.0–1.0, default 0.0)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>proven_only</code></td><td>bool</td><td>Only signal types proven to beat buy-and-hold (default false)</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>tradeable_only</code></td><td>bool</td><td>Only <code>conviction=strong</code> signals (default false)</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
      <h3>Response - Free Tier</h3>
      <pre><code set:html={signalsResponse} /></pre>
      <h3>Pro Tier Adds</h3>
      <p>Each signal object includes these additional fields:</p>
      <pre><code set:html={proFields} /></pre>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h2 id="signal-fields">Signal Fields</h2>
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>id</code></td><td>int</td><td>Unique signal ID</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>asset</code></td><td>string|null</td><td>Ticker symbol or null if market-wide</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>signal_type</code></td><td>string</td><td>regulatory, whale, sentiment, price, hack, listing, macro, macro_pulse, liquidation, funding, other</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>direction</code></td><td>string</td><td>bullish, bearish, neutral</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>urgency</code></td><td>string</td><td>high, medium, low</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>summary</code></td><td>string</td><td>Max 100 char description</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>confidence</code></td><td>float</td><td>0.0-1.0, calibrated P(win) — per-signal-type binned empirical win rate from closed-trade outcomes (not a raw LLM score). Updated weekly.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>conviction</code></td><td>string</td><td><code>strong</code>, <code>notable</code>, <code>watch</code>, <code>none</code> — our analytical rating of a signal's strength (not a trade instruction). <strong>strong</strong> is data-driven: it applies only to signal types whose forward-return record clears our statistical bar in paper-trading (see <a href="/proof">/proof</a>), at the top of that type's score distribution. Use this field.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>action_hint</code></td><td>string</td><td><em>Deprecated</em> — the prior name for <code>conviction</code> (<code>trade_signal</code>↔strong, <code>alert</code>↔notable, <code>monitor</code>↔watch, <code>ignore</code>↔none). Still emitted this release for backward compatibility; will be removed. Migrate to <code>conviction</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>corroborated</code></td><td>bool</td><td>True if multiple sources confirm</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>score</code></td><td>float</td><td>IC-weighted composite: source_weight x urgency x calibrated_confidence x signal-type information coefficient</td></tr>
